quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  22,24,"They have been guided to a wholesome way of talking as well as guided along the Praise worthy's road."
  22,25,"Those who disbelieve and obstruct Allah (God)'s way and (block) the Hallowed Mosque which We have granted to mankind on the same footing-whether the resident or the visitoryet We shall let anyone who wants to misuse it wrongfully, taste some painful torment. (IV)"
  22,26,"Thus We settled Abraham at the site of the House [saying]: "Do not associate anything with Me, "and purify My house for those who walk around it, and those who stand there [praying], and those who bow down and prostrate [in worship]."
  22,27,""Proclaim the Pilgrimage among mankind: they will come to you on foot and on every lean [beast of burden]; "let them come from every distant point,"
  22,28,"to gain benefits for themselves, and to mention Allah (God)'s name on appointed days over such heads of livestock [that they sacrifice] as He has provided them with. "So eat some of it and feed the needy pauper."
  22,29,"Then let them groom, fulfil their vows, and circle round the Ancient House (Kaaba).""
  22,30,"That is [how it should be], and it will be best with one's Lord for anyone who emphasizes Allah (God)'s restrictions. You are permitted livestock except for those which have been listed for you. Avoid the filth of idols and refrain from deceptive speech,"